    "updated_at": "2015-11-15T12:33:16Z",
    "body": "Yeah, but when the top menu bar is showing your mouse doesn't need to be active over it for the ctrl+r to work, your mouse can be anywhere on the screen and the ctrl+r works fine.\n\nHowever, when that top menu is gone and u have the dev console up, your **mouse has to be** active in the dev console  area for a ctrl+r or f5 to work.  But, when the top menu is there your mouse does not have to be active over it to work, doesn't seem right\n\nBasically I want to beable to refresh without having to  have the dev console screen open (and having my mouse over the dev console tab) without having a top menu.\n"
  },
