    "created_at": "2015-11-15T13:00:37Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-11-15T13:00:37Z",
    "body": "The dev console's shortcuts should only be active when it's opened, since they are related to dev things. Having ctrl+r being assigned to the same action in the rendered document and in the dev console is a coincidence. \nIf you want ctrl+r to work always the same way, you will have to declare a  [global shortcut](http://electron.atom.io/docs/v0.34.0/api/global-shortcut/)\n\n```\nvar globalShortcut = require('global-shortcut');\n\napp.on('ready', function() {\n  var ret = globalShortcut.register('ctrl+r', function() {\n    if (window.isFocused()) window.reload()\n  });\n\n});\n\napp.on('will-quit', function() {\n  globalShortcut.unregisterAll();\n});\n```\n"
  },
